# Approach
Iterating from the End: The algorithm starts iterating through the array from the end towards the beginning. The variable index is used to keep track of the last known position that can reach the end of the array.

Updating index: For each element in reverse order, check if the sum of the current element's value (nums[i]) and its index (i) is greater than or equal to the current value of index. If it is, update index to the current index i.

Final Check: After the loop finishes, if index is at the beginning (index 0), it means that you can jump from the start to the end of the array using the given jump values. In this case, return true, indicating that it's possible to reach the end. Otherwise, return false

